MemberInfoInitializer Interface

Definition

Defines methods that an external COM object must implement. This interface is used by an external COM implementation to expose its objects to JScript because JScript needs a managed MemberInfo to bind to an external object. This interface is implemented by COMFieldInfo, COMMethodInfo, and COMPropertyInfo.

In this Article

[System.Runtime.InteropServices.ComVisible(true)]
[System.Runtime.InteropServices.Guid("98A3BF0A-1B56-4f32-ACE0-594FEB27EC48")]
public interface MemberInfoInitializer

Methods

GetCOMMemberInfo()

When implemented in a class, gets a managed object that enables JScript to communicate with an external COM member.

public Microsoft.JScript.COMMemberInfo GetCOMMemberInfo ();
Returns
COMMemberInfo

A managed object that enables JScript to communicate with an external COM member.

Initialize(String, COMMemberInfo)

When implemented in a class, initializes the information that enables JScript to communicate with the specified external COM member.

public void Initialize (string name, Microsoft.JScript.COMMemberInfo dispatch);
Parameters
name
String

The name of the external COM member.

dispatch
COMMemberInfo

Information that enables JScript to call, get, and set the external COM member.
